  "prompt": "What is the best Italian restaurant in Seattle?",
  "response": "Identifying the \"best\" Italian restaurant in Seattle can be subjective, as it often depends on personal taste and what specific experience you're looking for. That said, several Italian restaurants in Seattle have been highly recommended by both locals and food critics. Some notable ones include:\n\n1. **Spinasse** - Known for its authentic Northern Italian cuisine, particularly its handmade pasta.\n2. **Il Corvo** - Famous for its daily-changing menu of fresh pasta and delicious sauces.\n3. **Osteria la Spiga** - Offers a range of traditional Italian dishes in a cozy setting, inspired by the Emilia-Romagna region.\n4. **Tavol\u00e0ta** - Appreciated for its rustic cooking with an emphasis on fresh, quality ingredients.\n5. **Barolo Ristorante** - Known for its elegant dining experience and modern Italian dishes.\n\nIt's always a good idea to check recent reviews and perhaps visit each restaurant's website to see their current menus and get updates on any new offerings.",
